name: West Shore Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: There are three unisex/family bathrooms.  Enter from the parking lot entrance (east entrance).  The most commonly used by the public are directly forward through the rotunda.  Take the first hallway on your left that does not have a door.  Turn left again and there are two bathrooms right there.  There is a unisex bathroom to your right and all the way down the small hallway.
comment: This is a church and is open 8AM to 10PM Monday through Friday, most Saturdays during the day, and during the morning and afternoon on Sundays.The 2009-10 intern minister is/was genderqueer and the congregation is a welcoming congregation to the GLBT community.

name: Chipotle

name: Chipotle Mexican Restaurant

comment: Open 11AM to 10 PM.If it's busy, no one will even notice if you come in to use the bathroom and leave.  Otherwise, just buy a drink.

comment: The baristas there are some of the sweetest people you'll meet, I'd honestly be shocked if they told you off for using the bathroom without buying something. They won't care. They do make awesome coffee though.

name: Louis Stokes V.A. Medical Center
directions:
There are both stall type and Unisex. Usually located along main hallways. 

This is a federal hospital run for military vets but it is public. There are restrooms on second floor across the new pedestrian bridge. Go back by the elevators and turn left-you'll see the signs. Ladies to the right, men to the left.
comment:
Here's what most non-veteran transgenders are missing-http://www.cristanwilliams.com/b/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/VHADirective2013.pdf

The V.A. has issued directives for its employees detailing 
how transgender vets are to be treated, respected and cared for. V.A. security isn't going to question your presence as long as you are respectful so use our facilities. Hugs.

directions: Resteroom is a single occupancy with sink that's labled "family" (there are RR's labled by binary gender too) and it's directly off of the lobby down the first halway on the left.
comment:
I am not certain if it's handicap accessible but there are no steps.

You may want to call to check that they're open. (513) 272-2002  I don't know if you can get in without someone greeting you at the ticket 
booth or concession stand, since this place is so small. You may still be able to get to the restroom without buying a ticket since they don't collect tickets until you get deeper into the theater. I returned after a show in a small group and no one asked for our tickets.

This is a small artsy theater in an upper middle class area. They serve wine and fruit in their concession stand. The staff were friendly, even when I wasn't passing. It's on the main square in the middle of the strip mall. There's parking in the center of the square.

comment: You'll have to be buzzed in unless there's an event or service. Say you're there for a safe restroom when they ask how they can help you on the intercom. M-F hours are 8:30am-4:30pm. Sunday 7:00am-1:00pm and some times 4:30-6:30pm.

name: Shell
comment: You just have to go in and ask for the key from the cashier, don't have to be paying customer.

name: Wyoming Rec Center
street: 9940 Springfield Pike Cincinnati, OH  45215 United States
directions: Walk into the pool area and turn left, there will be two single-stall family restrooms on either side of the water fountain
comment: You have to pay to get into the pool, membership or one-time purchase

name: TriCounty Mall
directions: First floor of the mall, near the store entrance to Macy's. It is a single-user lockable 'family' restroom off a small hallway kitty-corner from the  fountain and furniture area.
comment: Official hours are M-S 10-9, Sun 12-6, though the mall doors are generally open for an hour or two before and after the "official" hours.

name: Sidewinder Coffee
comment: Restrooms are labelled "Men" and "Women", but this coffee shop has a large transgender and gender queer clientele and employees.

name: Om Cafe
directions: Back of store, to right of counter
comment: There are two, single-stall, unisex bathrooms for customers and people attending events.

name: Village Green Foundation
directions: Unisex bathroom in the basement past all the bike parts. This is the only public bathroom in the building, so there aren't any accessible bathrooms.
comment: Open hours may vary for each program of the Village Green Foundation. Check websites/social media for MoBo, Village Green Gardens, and Soapbox Books & Zines for current open hours.

name: Target
directions: Just inside the door, on the way to the main restrooms

name: Target
directions: on the left after entering front doors

name: Target

name: French Hall West

comment: Everyone in this building is super friendly, but also give you your space, so do not worry about being questioned. They'll help you find it if you get lost.

name: French Hall West
directions: On School of Social Work's floor of building (first floor), across from School of Social Work's reception desk, near the other restrooms.
comment: Everyone in this building is super friendly, but also give you your space, so do not worry about being questioned. They'll help you find it if you get lost.

directions: It is located on the second floor near the women's jeans. It is labeled as a "family" restroom, but it is unisex and accessible. It is to the right of the women's restroom.

comment: Langsam Computer Lab is open 24/7. After 10pm it can be accessed through the outside stairs to the left of the 4th floor entrance (main) or through the elevator in the 4th floor entrance.

comment: open even when there isn't soccer games, free to the public.

comment: Four individual bathrooms, not gender segregated, have toilet and shower, and hair dryer.

name: Colerain Old Navy

name: Arcade Legacy: Bar Edition
directions: Straight back from the entrance in its own hallway.
comment:
Two unisex rooms with locks. Both have drawings of Samus. No gendered rooms, so no questions will be asked. 

It's a bar that checks IDs, so 21+ most likely.

name: Menards
directions: Up front by the registers. There is a hall way that dead ends into the men's and women's restrooms. There is a door on the left side of the hallway that is a non-gender one stall bathroom

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back right of the store.

name: Esquire Theatre
directions: Down the hallway in the back, directly across from the small bar.
comment: If you're a "paying customer" you'll be totally fine. It might be more difficult if you aren't simply because the bathroom is past concessions and they might suspect you're trying to sneak into a movie. But if if you're comfortable enough to ask to use the gender neutral restroom in the back most of the employees probably wouldn't care at all.

name: Red Tree Gallery and Coffee Shop
comment: Two bathrooms. Both used to be gendered and were recently remodeled and are now gender neutral. Both are handicap accessible and are single bathrooms/stalls. There's a ramp in the building and two entrances so you can avoid the stairs if need be. One is next to the back entrance, one is right behind the counter. If you want to be more discrete, go in the back entrance and use the bathroom there.

name: Blegen Library
directions: Main floor (4th floor). Go around the Classics office (i.e. if you are staring at the classics door go to the left and the bathroom is off a tiny hallway to the right. Bathroom is then on the left. It is super hard to find but definitely there.
comment: If you have a hard time finding it and are uncomfortable asking where it is, ask someone to show you where the elevator is to the Archives/Rare Books Library; you'll see it next to that elevator - different from the main elevators for the building.

name: Lindner Center - University Health Services
directions: Located in the mental health waiting room, down the hall from the main health clinic, across from the Student Health Insurance Office.
comment: Single bathroom/stall. You don't have to be a patient or waiting on an appointment to go into the waiting room and use the bathroom. There are noise machines so nobody in surrounding offices/walls can hear you.

name: Chipotle
directions: In the back of the store

name: Chatham College

comment: It's a cute queer-owned neighborhood cafe & breakfast favorite.  The bathrooms even have cute chalk boards if you want to leave a message.Hours:Monday-Saturday 7am-3pmSunday 8am-3pmt 412.244.8002

name: Bellefield Hall

Second floor has two unisex restrooms on the north side, near the weight room.

comment: Bellefield Hall requires Pitt ID for 'recreational use', but classes, purchasing software from the Student Software Sales office, and visiting offices are exempt.  Offices in the building include  University Times, CSSD administration, campus YMCA, and Army ROTC.

name: Rickert & Beagle Books

comment: I am posting this as the owner of the store. If you need access to my bathroom come in and use my bathroom!

name: Chatham University
directions: There are gender neutral / unisex bathrooms in most of the buildings. To get to the ones in the dorms, you need a student card. To the more public areas, there is the Anderson dining hall and Carriage House. The dining hall one is on the upper floor near the entrance of the cafeteria and is sort of wheelchair accessible. If you come from the main road then the entrance is right there. But if you come from down the hill and the dorms then you have to go up another hill leading to the side of the hall and the back of the AFC to get to the main road entrance. The Carriage House is in the same area as the other bathrooms and is wheelchair accessible.

name: Whitfield Hall
directions: Building entrance at porch around back. Downstairs to the right of the stairs. I was in the women's bathroom and it had extra pads and tampons.
comment: Probably need to be in hall for a reason, though might be able to stop and ask to use the restroom.

name: Beechwood Farms Nature Reserve
directions: Located in gift shop towards back.

name: Nordstroms-Ross Park Mall
directions: Single family bathroom on 2nd floor

name: Planned Parenthood
comment: Available for health center patients.

name: East Liberty Presbyterian Church
directions:
All the RR have signs indicating that ELPC welcomes gender diversity. Please feel free to use the RR that fits your gender identity or expression. 

Men's is to the right and women's straight ahead.
comment: There is a table to sign in at when you come in. It is a safe and welcoming space based on what I have seen.

name: Ace Hotel
directions: basement with elevator access

name: Ace Hotel
directions: basement, with elevator access

name: Ace Hotel
directions: basement with elevator access

name: Eat n Park
directions: upon entering, turn left and walk as far that way as possible, then right and you will see it there.
comment: in my experience, they let me in without buying anything. however, i'm also a regular so i'm not sure about others. -g.avery

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Back left corner of the store

name: ikea
directions: top floor, behind food counter down a long hallway is a family restroom!
comment: usable as long as you're shopping at ikea!

name: Ppg Paints Arena
directions: Family bathrooms are all over the place near the food stands and bars

name: Texas Roadhouse
directions: In back corner of restaurant by women’s restroom. Past the bar.
comment: It is a “family restroom.”

name: Purnell Center for the Arts, Carnegie Mellon campus
directions: All floors have single use accessible restrooms.

name: Gap
directions: Go downstairs or down the elevator to the Gap Kids department
comment: Just ask the cashier if they have a restroom and they can let you in with their key. Keep in mind that this is in a kids department and kids are weird sometimes. There are two single stall restrooms and both are unmarked

name: Starbucks
directions: 2 single stalls in the back left. Door code is 0100

name: Grant street transportation center
directions: Between the male and female restrooms and across bus door number 9.
comment: Not always open or locked often.

name: PERSAD Center (aka Equality Center)
comment: LGBT-centered company. Has a neutral bathroom in lobby. Just ask the person at the front desk.

name: Piada Italian Street Food
directions: There’s a ramp that says “bathrooms” over it on the left side of the restaurant. Family bathroom is the first door.

name: 61B Cafe
directions: Ground floor, back, left.

name: Cathedral of Learning
directions: G-2 -- on the ground floor, so if you are on the floor with the main hall, go down one floor to G (any stairwell or elevator). follow signs to copy center/mail. Signed as "family/inclusive restroom".
comment: Accessible. Open to the public during the day. University ID required after around 11pm.

name: Artisan Cafe
directions: first floor, to the back, door is on the left
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer. You are welcome. It is a safe space to hang out, do work, read, talk, anything really. all is welcome.

name: Morewood Gardens
directions: On the first floor of Morewood Gardens, behind the kitchen and next to the vending machines.
comment: You must present a CMU ID at the front desk for building access.

name: City Works
directions: First door on the left in bathroom hallway
comment: Say you’re going to order at the bar to bypass waitstaff, then turn left.

name: Central Outreach Wellness Center
directions: In the medical clinic office space.
comment: Must be getting an STD check, but its free

name: Tiki Lounge
directions: Bottom floor, Men’s and Women’s gender neutral
comment: both restrooms are gender neutral

name: Trixie’s Bar
directions: back of bar
comment: both bathrooms - gender neutral

name: CCAC North Campus Library
directions: After entering the front doors of the building, proceed straight and the library will be on your right. Signage is good, so look for the library sign. The gender neutral restroom is located on the first floor of the library. Enter the library, walk past the stairs that lead to the second floor, go around the corner to the left, and then straight back past the reference desk. The restroom is at the far end of the room.

name: S&D Polish Deli
comment: No good for pooping, as the door opens directly into a dining area

name: Hillman Center for Performing Arts
directions: lower level, next to the green room: near the theater’s emergency/handicap accessible exit/entrance
comment: if you’re on campus for an event at the Hillman, this is the one family bathroom in the building

name: Human Services Building
directions: Take elevator to lower level, gender neutral bathroom is to left.
comment: Say you have a meeting in Rachel Carson room and sign in if you are stopped by security guard.

name: Mad Mex Waterworks
comment: Not sure on accessible or changing table

name: Burger King
comment: Gendered single stall

name: Golden Palace Buffet
comment: There seems to be only one bathroom, marked men's?

name: Greyhound Bus Station
directions: Just past vending machines on the right.
comment: Gender neutral bathroom is always locked. Not sure if you have to ask for keys or something. Been harassed in the men’s restroom.

name: Katana
directions: Hallway in very back
comment: Not actually single stall, but the entire bathroom is lockable (at least the men's room is)

name: Blaine
directions: On third and fifth floors
comment: Only accessible when the school is having a performance. You’d have to pay to get in, and even then I’d ask if it would be okay to use.

name: Bangkok Balcony
comment: Gendered single stall. Signage on the women's room is kind of ambiguous

name: Escape Room PGH
directions: Follow the hallway all the way back til you're in the bathroom

name: honeygrow
directions: Directly to the left from the counter, easily able to use without being a paying customer

name: City-County Building
directions: On the first floor of the building, go to the City Controller's offices and there's a safe, public women's restroom in that lobby area

name: Kristen
directions: Ground floor next to the coat rack

name: Aquinas
directions: Ground floor by the coat rack
comment: You have to have a Carlow University swipe to get into the building

name: Millie's Summer of Soft Serve
directions: When you enter, it's to the left, down a short hallway.
comment: I believe you have to be a paying customer.

name: Driftwood Oven
directions: Back of restaurant, to the left
comment: Single-person/family restrooms labeled w amenities rather than gender. Must be a paying customer.

name: Mad Mex Shadyside
directions: Past the bar, down the restroom hallway all the way to the end of the hall.
comment: Large family restroom that can be used by anyone of any gender. A favorite with my trans son.

name: The Magic Noodle
directions: Back of restaurant
comment: All gender accessible restroom on first floor. Single stall men & women rooms on second floor.

name: Everyday Noodles
directions: On the back to the left
comment: Need to be paying customer; you can just buy a to-go tea. Accessibility is dubious — there’s enough room but people crowd into the aisle and there aren’t bars in the restrooms. Both restrooms are gendered single-occupancy.

name: Cathedral of Learning
directions: Ground floor, near the vending machines.
comment: Need student ID past 11:00 PM.

name: Ineffable Ca Phe
directions: Go through front room, turn right down the hallway. There’s a huge sign on the wall saying NEUTRAL RESTROOMS
comment:
Large sign saying Neutral Restrooms. One is labeled men/women/accessible (multistall, changing table) & the other men/accessible (one stall one open urinal)

Paying customers only

name: Black Forge Coffee
directions: Ground floor back
comment: LGBTQ2+ FRIENDLY heavy metal coffee shop

name: Black Forge Coffee
directions: Ground floor back
comment: LGBTQ2 + FRIENDLY HEAVY METAL COFFEE SHOP AND VENUE ALL AGES

name: Black Forge Coffee House
directions: In the back
comment: LGBTQ2 + FRIENDLY HEAVY METAL COFFEE SHOP

name: Frick Environmental Center
directions:
First floor next to the other bathrooms. Second floor, it is the only bathroom. There is an elevator. Both of these have changing tables.

Outside of the building near the parking lot there are two more bathrooms.
comment: Open to the public.

name: Banh Mi & Ti
comment: Paying customer.

name: Rose Tea Cafe
directions: Up the ramp, to the back
comment: Paying customer. Door on ladies room says Koala Bear Care but there’s no changing table

name: Pie for Breakfast
directions: Right by the host stand
comment: Two restrooms, one labeled “all gender with urinal” (not accessible, changing table, one stall w urinal in common space) and one “all gender” (accessible).

name: Point Park Academic Hall
directions: Acedemic Hall entrance behind glass wall.
comment: Need a student id to enter building

name: William Pitt Union
directions:
Floor 6, room 618 - next to elevators
Floor 8, room 818
comment: May not be accessible at all times for those who are not Pitt students and faculty

name: La Palapa
directions: Ground floor, first left by the stairs. Pretty sure is accessible
comment: Have to be a paying customer, nice staff so if it’s an emergency then they’d probably let you in

name: Giant Eagle
directions: All the way to the back and on the right by the bakery and tables. Is a single stall and is in good shape
comment: Can go straight in and no one cares.

name: Eat Unique
directions: Second level of the cafe, through the doors, in the back next to the stairs
comment: You can come in the front door and go straight into the eating section, turn right and go up the stairs, then go through the white door. I’m not sure if you need to pay but this will avoid interactions with any employees!

name: Carnegie Museum of Natural History
directions: Past the big dinosaur room, through the water room, and to the right on the back wall of the discovery base camp. Family stall
comment: Need to pay admission

name: Carnegie Museum of Art
directions: in the Scaife gallery
comment: paid admission

name: Katana
directions: Back of first floor

name: Kiin Lao & Thai Eatery
comment: Gendered single stall. Doors are more gender-marked than when this was Bangkok Balcony

name: Victory Pointe Arcade
directions: Same floor as entrance. Staff will point you to it.
comment: You technically have to be a paying customer, but if you’re nice then they’ll probably let you in. They also have a cafe if you need to buy a low cost thing to use the bathroom.

name: Target
directions: Turn right off of the elevator or escalator and the restrooms are on your right side, before the pharmacy. The family restroom is on your right side across from the gendered restrooms.

name: Chatham University: Science Complex: Laboratory Building and Buhl Hall
directions: "All gender" single occupancy restroom. On floor one (not basement/floor zero) opposite the women's bathroom. Converted previous men's room with urinal and single large stall including hand bars. Main door and stall both lock. Enter through west side door and turn right for shortest route door-to-bathroom.
comment: The bathroom is available for people in the Chatham community, such as students, faculty & staff and their families, people touring the campus, and event attendees.

name: Salud Juicery
directions: Walk directly to the back on the left side. You will see the door.
